Winter is coming to Gaza, where some 100,000 people have been left homeless.
On Twitter,
[@NourAlghussein](https://twitter.com/NourAlGhussein/status/515911848042844160)
says: “winter is on the doors here .and Gaza is still besieged >there's no
materials to rebuild these houses #BreakGazaSiege”

After the [intense
destruction](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/gaza-civilian-
death-toll-mounts-in-israeli-offensive/) caused by [this summer's
war](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2014_Israel%E2%80%93Gaza_conflict),
thousands of Gazans are left with insufficient resources to brave winter's
coming cold.

The United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA)
[reported](http://www.ochaopt.org/documents/ocha_opt_protection_of_civilians_weekly_report_2014_10_17_english.pdf)
in October 2014 that an estimated 20,000 homes were destroyed, displacing
100,000 people. Refugees either live with host families or in collective
centers, like schools.

On Twitter, the first rains of autumn spurred concern for the refugees’
future.

> If You Want To See How People In
> [#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash) Spend The Winter This
> Year Here Is A Sample For You Sir/Madam
> …[#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash)
> [#Winter](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Winter?src=hash)
> [pic.twitter.com/DFvnoXGcc0](http://t.co/DFvnoXGcc0)
>
> — Salah AlQady (@salah_alqady) [October 19,
> 2014](https://twitter.com/salah_alqady/status/523954633224757248)

> Heavy rains in [#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash). First
> winter storm to hit since the end of war, with thousands of families
> displaced or living in damaged homes
>
> — Fares Akram (@faresakram) [October 19,
> 2014](https://twitter.com/faresakram/status/523734809026527232)

Blogger Omar Ghraieb, who is based in Gaza, wrote:

> It hasnt stopped raining since the morning & I havent stopped praying &
> thinking about displaced & homeless people here & everywhere.
> [#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash)
>
> — Omar Ghraieb (@Omar_Gaza) [October 19,
> 2014](https://twitter.com/Omar_Gaza/status/523790513254576128)

Later that day, he added:

> [#Photo](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Photo?src=hash): Displaced Palestinians
> in [#KhanYounis](https://twitter.com/hashtag/KhanYounis?src=hash) trying to
> stop rain floods 4m washing away their tents\caravans!
> [#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash)
> [pic.twitter.com/et1I5oWAby](http://t.co/et1I5oWAby)
>
